\n    return matrix", "holes": {"replace_black_with_blue_below_maroon": "For each column, if there are maroon pixels, replace all black pixels below maroon pixels with blue", "has_maroon_without_green": "Return whether there are maroon pixels and no green pixels", "get_width": "Return the width", "get_min_max_rows_of_maroon": "Return the minimun row and maximun row of maroon pixels", "replace_pixels_with_green": "Replace the black and blue pixels of the matrix from row r1-gap to row r2+gap, and from column j-gap to column j+gap+r2-r1 with green"}}
